Version 0.3.13, please upgrade

Bitcointalk

2010-10-01 00:34:35 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Version 0.3.13 is now available.  You should upgrade to prevent
   potential problems with 0/unconfirmed transactions.  Note: 0.3.13
   prevents problems if you havenʼt already spent a 0/unconfirmed
   transaction, but if that already happened, you need 0.3.13.2.
   Changes:
   - Donʼt count or spend payments until they have 1 confirmation.
   - Internal version number from 312 to 31300.
   - Only accept transactions sent by IP address if -allowreceivebyip is
   specified.
   - Dropped DB_PRIVATE Berkeley DB flag.
   - Fix problem sending the last cent with sub-cent fractional change.
   - Auto-detect whether to use 128-bit 4-way SSE2 on Linux.
   Gavin Andresen:
   - Option -rpcallowip= to accept json-rpc connections from another
   machine.
   - Clean shutdown on SIGTERM on Linux.
   Download:
   [12]http://sourceforge.net/projects/bitcoin/files/Bitcoin/bitcoin-0.3.1
   3/
   (Thanks Laszlo for the Mac OSX build!)
   Note:
   The SSE2 auto-detect in the Linux 64-bit version doesnʼt work with AMD
   in 64-bit mode.  Please try this instead and let me know if it gets it
   right:
   [13]http://www.bitcoin.org/download/bitcoin-0.3.13.1-specialbuild-linux
   64.tar.gz
   You can still control the SSE2 use manually with -4way and -4way=0.
   Version 0.3.13.2 (SVN rev 161) has improvements for the case where you
   already had 0/unconfirmed transactions that you might have already
   spent.  Hereʼs a Windows build of it:
   [14]http://www.bitcoin.org/download/bitcoin-0.3.13.2-win32-setup.exe
